vbss_ac is user application to simulate VBSS AC.
vbss_ac is supported on ARM (CLS D1K) and X86 Ubuntu platform. vbss_ac is tested
on x86_64 20.04.1-Ubuntu with gcc (Ubuntu 9.4.0-1ubuntu1~20.04.2) 9.4.0.

1. Compilation
(1) get vbss_ac.c and vbss.h. Put them in same folder.
(2) gcc vbss_ac.c -o vbss_ac-x86
(3) chmod +x vbss_ac-x86
(4) ./vbss_ac-x86 <cmds>


2. Topology
             PC(vbss_ac)
                 |
---------------Switch----------------
|                                   |
AP1(vbss_agent)                  AP2(vbss_agent)

3. Usage
$ ./vbss_ac-x86 ?
Usage:
  vbss_ac <cmd> <param>
  cmds:
    ping          <agent IP>
    enable_vbss   <agent IP> <primary ifname> <0 | 1>
    add_vap       <agent IP> <ifname> <bssid> <ssid> <wpa2 | open> [key]
    copy_vap_info <src IP> <ifname> <dest IP> <ifname>
    del_vap       <agent IP> <ifname>
    copy_sta_info <sta mac> <src IP> <ifname> <dest IP> <ifname>
    roam_sta      <sta mac> <src IP> <ifname> <dest IP> <ifname>
    trg_switch    <sta mac> <src IP> <ifname> <dest IP> <ifname>
    switch_done   <sta mac> <src IP> <ifname> <dest IP> <ifname>

Note: MAC address format: 00:11:22:33:44:55

4. Use vbss_ac to control VBSS
Give an example to show the usage of vbss_ac. The configuration of the example:
IP_AP1=10.30.9.159
IP_AP2=10.30.21.76
VBSS VAP BSSID=D0:44:33:00:00:45
VBSS VAP BSSID=VBSS_Demo
VBSS VAP auth=WPA2-PSK
VBSS VAP key=12345678
STA MAC=BC:09:1B:24:3E:0C

Steps to roam STA from AP1 to AP2:
(1) Setup PC, AP1 and AP2 as topology shown. Make sure there are network available.
(2) 'vbss_agent &' on AP1 and AP2.
    Lauch vbss_agent on AP1 and AP2.
(3) Follwing cmds are executed on PC(vbss_ac).
    (a) ./vbss_ac-x86 ping 10.30.9.159
        Test connection between vbss_ac and AP1 vbss_agent.
    (b) ./vbss_ac-x86 ping 10.30.21.76
        Test connection between vbss_ac and AP2 vbss_agent.
    (c) ./vbss_ac-x86 enable_vbss 10.30.9.159 wlan1 1
        Enable VBSS on AP1.
    (d) ./vbss_ac-x86 enable_vbss 10.30.21.76 wlan1 1
        Enable VBSS on AP2.
    (e) ./vbss_ac-x86 add_vap 10.30.9.159 wlan1_1 D0:44:33:00:00:45 VBSS_Demo wpa2 12345678
        Add VBSS VAP wlan1_1 on AP1.
    (f) ./vbss_ac-x86 roam_sta BC:09:1B:24:3E:0C 10.30.9.159 wlan1_1 10.30.21.76 wlan1_1
        After STA associats AP1, roam STA from AP1 to AP2.
    (g) ./vbss_ac-x86 roam_sta BC:09:1B:24:3E:0C 10.30.21.76 wlan1_1 10.30.9.159 wlan1_1
        Roam STA from AP2 to AP1.

